# Smart Temperature Control System Using Arduino and TMP36 Sensor

## Project Overview
This project implements a Smart Temperature Control System using Arduino Uno and a TMP36 temperature sensor. The system continuously monitors temperature and automatically controls an LED based on a predefined threshold value.

## Components Used
* Arduino Uno
* TMP36 Temperature Sensor
* LED
* 220Ω Resistor
* Jumper Wires
* Tinkercad Simulator

## Circuit Connections
### TMP36 Sensor
* Left Pin → 5V
* Middle Pin → A0
* Right Pin → GND
### LED
* Long Leg (+) → Arduino Pin 7 through 220Ω resistor
* Short Leg (-) → GND

## Working
The TMP36 sensor measures temperature and sends analog values to the Arduino. The Arduino converts these values into temperature readings and displays them on the Serial Monitor.

If the temperature exceeds 30°C:
* LED turns ON
If the temperature is below 30°C:
* LED turns OFF

## Automation Logic
Temperature > 30°C → LED ON
Temperature ≤ 30°C → LED OFF

## Results
The project successfully demonstrates sensor monitoring, automation logic, and output control using Arduino.

## Future Enhancement
The system can be extended using ESP32 and cloud platforms such as ThingSpeak or Blynk for IoT-based remote monitoring and control.
